<item>
            <title>[LU-10199] sanity test_56xb: hard links individually migrated (12 != 11)</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10199</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for Bob Glossman &amp;lt;bob.glossman@intel.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/740cdf26-c31d-11e7-88ab-52540065bddc&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/740cdf26-c31d-11e7-88ab-52540065bddc&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The sub-test test_56xb failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;hard links individually migrated (12 != 11)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;strongly suspect this is due to the very recently landed &quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6051&quot; title=&quot;&amp;quot;lfs_migrate&amp;quot; improvements&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-6051&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-6051&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; utils: allow lfs_migrate to handle hard links&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
test 56xb is brand new, only introduced in this patch.&lt;br/&gt;
I&apos;m wondering if this test has ever been passed on any SLES version.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Info required for matching: sanity 56xb&lt;/p&gt;</description>
