                            <comment id="224492" author="adilger" created="Sun, 25 Mar 2018 04:01:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This problem is not fixed, only the test is in ALWAYS_EXCEPT on master. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As a general rule, any ticket with the &lt;tt&gt;always_except&lt;/tt&gt; label should not be closed. This label should be removed when the patch that re-enables the test is landed. I&apos;ve often found, as in this case, that a ticket is marked resolved, but the reason the test is no longer failing is because the test has been disabled. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
